Attorney General John Ashcroft was cleared of violating anti-lobbying laws for promoting the Patriot Act in speeches.
The Act, passed after 9/11, expanded law enforcement powers against terrorists.
President Bush praised Ashcroft's efforts in counterterrorism.
Critics argue the Act infringes on civil liberties, with controversial provisions like obtaining library records.
A coalition, Patriots to Restore Checks and Balances, aims to repeal key Act provisions.
Some conservatives and the ACLU seek to amend the Act for privacy safeguards.
The debate over renewing the Patriot Act continues, with concerns about balancing security and freedom.
